","pid":"121783","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/121783/1827e127-d913-427a-8a3e-476e38757653.png","stmt":"I’m proud to be standing for the Liberal Democrats as your local candidate for Chadderton North in the elections on Thursday 7th May.\n\nRight now, Oldham Council aren’t getting the basics right. Residents are facing rising council tax, while everyday issues like potholes and road safety, especially around Chadderton roundabout, are being ignored.\n\nAt the same time, money is being spent on projects that don’t reflect what local people actually want.\n\nThat needs to change.\n\nI’m standing because Chadderton North deserves a councillor who listens and acts on residents’ concerns. I want to see more investment in our area, safer roads, and a council that focuses on delivering real value for taxpayers.\n\nFor years, Liberal Democrat councillors in Oldham have worked hard to hold the administration to account. With your support, we can go further and deliver real change.\n\nVote Liberal Democrats this May.\nVote for a fair deal for Oldham.","tw":"\"premraghvani\"","url":"\"https://premraghvani.com/\"","li":"\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/premraghvani/\""}]},{"ward":"Chadderton South","seats":1,"turnout_pct":41.8,"results_url":"https://www.oldham.gov.uk/election_results_may7_2026","candidates":[{"n":"Rob Jackson","p":"Reform UK","v":1833,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129696","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/129696/309e149c-7cf2-4367-9c69-34edfd2749fa.png"},{"n":"Kyle Phythian","p":"Labour and Co-operative Party","v":709,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"81296","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/81296/51610299-f722-4e36-b587-be5409b4c864.png","tw":"\"kylephythian\""},{"n":"Stephanie Anne Beverley","p":"Green Party","v":539,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129693","img":